      "message": "Line 85: 🟡 Suggestions: Initializing the smoothed loss state to 0 changes the first RTCP adaptation result from the previous 10% default to 0% when the first report has no loss. Since `packetLoss_` still defaults to 10, this creates an abrupt startup behavior change and can immediately drive audio bitrate adaptation differently than before. Keep the smoothing state aligned with the existing default unless this behavior change is intentional and covered by tests.\n```suggestion\n    float pondLoss_ {10.0f};\n```",
