      "message": "[Critical] Line 636: 🔴 Critical Issues: `accountBytes()` consumes bandwidth tokens for RTCP before RTP is evaluated, so under a constrained simulator RTCP can spend the shared budget and cause media RTP to be dropped, which works against the stated goal of preserving audio quality and makes simulator results dependent on feedback traffic volume. If RTCP must never be dropped, it also should not starve RTP in this in-process QoS simulator; either do not account RTCP against the drop budget, or use separate accounting that does not reduce RTP tokens.\n```suggestion\n        if (!isRTCP \u0026\u0026 !sim-\u003eshouldSend(static_cast\u003csize_t\u003e(buf_size))) {\n            return buf_size;\n        }\n```",
